section#manifesto.spotlight.style2.bottom
  span.image.fit.main
    img alt="" src="img/pic02.png" /
  .content
    .container
      .row
        .4u class="12u$(medium)" 
          header
            h3 There's nothing wrong with the <br>original Agile Manifesto.
            p <br>It succeeded beyond our wildest dreams. Closed to modification but open to extension, it's the <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/pulse/xp-beats-heart-agile-peter-merel">beating heart</a> of all Agile methods. 
            p The original manifesto focuses on Agile teams, not organizations. As Agile organizations are composed entirely of these teams, they naturally apply the <a href="http://agilemanifesto.org">original values</a> at all levels and to all business functions.
            p However the <a href="http://agilemanifesto.org/principles.html">original principles</a> of the manifesto don't apply to the organization of teams. Likewise the early Agile value of <a href="http://www.extremeprogramming.org/rules/collective.html">collective ownership</a>, too extreme for the first manifesto, is now critical to Agile Organizations as decentralized ecosystems</a>.
        .4u class="12u$(medium)" 
          h3 Agile Organization Values 
          p 
            | We are uncovering better ways of organizing value streams by doing so and helping others do so. Through this work we have come to value:
            ul
              li <a href="http://xscale.wiki/#Team%20Representation">Individuals and interactions</a> <br>over processses and tools
              li <a href="http://xscale.wiki/#Throughput">Business throughput</a> <br>over cost minimization
              li <a href="http://xscale.wiki/#Consensus%20Decision-Making">Customer collaboration</a> <br>over contract negotiation
              li <a href="http://xscale.wiki/#Throughput%20Accounting">Responding to change</a> <br>over following a plan
              li <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/pulse/xscale-alliance-seeking-worlds-best-agile-trainers-coaches-merel">Decentralized ownership</a> <br>over delegating control  
              br That is, while there is value in the items on the bottom, we value the items on the top more.
        div class=("4u$ 12u$(medium)") 
          h3 Agile Organization Principles
          p
            | Agile Organization is a pod of dolphins, not a dancing elephant. It doesn't scale Agile to the organization. It de-scales organization to Agile via:
            ul
              li <a href="http://xscale.wiki/#XSCALE%20Principles">eXponential</a> return by stacking growth curves.
              li  &nbsp;&nbsp;<a href="http://xscale.wiki/#XSCALE%20Principles">Simple</a> design to the elegance of minimum. 
              li  &nbsp;&nbsp;<a href="http://xscale.wiki/#XSCALE%20Principles">Continuous</a> optimization of throughput.
              li  &nbsp;&nbsp;<a href="http://xscale.wiki/#XSCALE%20Principles">Autonomous</a> teams, self-managing streams.
              li  &nbsp;&nbsp;<a href="http://xscale.wiki/#XSCALE%20Principles">Learning</a>: triple loop, breadth-first, set-based.
              li  &nbsp;&nbsp;<a href="http://xscale.wiki/#XSCALE%20Principles">Ecosystems</a> thinking: whole-board & win-win.
            p
              | Per the original Manifesto, we uphold these values and principles as <a href="https://drive.google.com/file/d/0BwhCYaYDn8EgN2M5MTkwM2EtNWFkZC00ZTI3LWFjZTUtNTFhZGZiYmUzODc1/view">closed to modification but open to extension</a>. The XSCALE Manifesto isn't the last word in Agility; we regard it as the next.
