      p What's the difference?
      p Agile teams help people self-organize efficiently.<br>Scaling adapts Agile to traditional management.<br>Agile Organization helps teams self-manage:
      ul
        li <a href="http://xscale.wiki/#Product%20Management">Exponential Product Management</a> aligns design, business and tech authorities breadth-first to optimize ecosystem throughput
        li <a href="http://xscale.wiki/#Holarchy">Holarchic Portfolios</a> empower doers in decisions to prevent politics & disconnects
        li <a href="http://xscale.wiki/#Organization%20Permaculture">Organization Permaculture</a> minimizes costs of quality and delay by combining Agile with DevOps and "open-book" Throughput Accounting
        li <a href="#transformation">Exponential Transformation</a> generates new capability without compromise or confusion
